description.p:
WO02/096215 discloses a method of fractionation of a protein containing mixture wherein the protein containing mixture is selected from the group consisting of milk, milk-derived products, milk derived raw materials, vegetable derived products, vegetable derived extracts, fruit derived products, fruit derived extracts, fish derived products, and fish derived extracts, said method comprising the steps of:
(a) optionally adjusting the pH of the mixture;
(b) applying said mixture to an adsorption column comprising an adsorbent, said adsorbent comprises a particle with at least one high density non-porous core surrounded by a porous material, the adsorbent having a particle density of at least 1.5 g/ml and a mean volume particle size of at most 150 µm;
(c) optionally washing the column;
(d) eluting at least one protein from the adsorbent.

Thus, the present invention provides a process for the large-scale isolation of proteins from a protein solution wherein the protein solution is obtained from human blood, such as human serum and/or human plasma, in which process albumin and IgG are separated from one another, said process comprising the steps of:
a) optionally adjusting the pH of the protein solution to a preset pH;
b) optionally adjusting the ionic strength or conductivity of the protein solution to a preset ionic strength or a preset conductivity;
c) applying said protein solution to an adsorption column comprising an adsorbent, said adsorbent comprises a particle with at least one high density non-porous core, surrounded by a porous material, the adsorbent comprises a particle density of at least 1.5 g/ml and a mean volume particle diameter of at most 150 µm;
d) washing one or more of the proteins to be isolated through the adsorbent, without the one or more proteins having been specifically bound to the adsorbent, to obtain a non-bound material fraction;
e) subjecting the adsorbent to an elution buffer to elute at least one of the proteins specifically bound to the adsorbent; wherein either:
albumin and IgG are obtained from the adsorbent by stepwise elution; or
albumin is obtained as non-bound material from the adsorbent and subsequently IgG is obtained from the adsorbent by stepwise elution.

In a cascade of 3 adsorbents the following process may occur:
a) the first adsorbent is capable of capturing one or more blood protein(s), serum protein(s) or plasma protein(s);
b) the second adsorbent is capable of capturing one or more blood protein(s), serum protein(s) or plasma protein(s) different for the one or more blood protein(s), serum protein(s) or plasma protein(s) capable of being captured to the first adsorbent; and
c) the third adsorbent is capable of capturing one or more blood protein(s), serum protein(s) or plasma protein(s) different for the one or more blood protein(s), serum protein(s) or plasma protein(s) capable of being captured to the first adsorbent or second adsorbent;

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren im großen Maßstab zur Isolation von Proteinen aus einer Proteinlösung, wobei die Proteinlösung aus menschlichem Blut wie etwa menschliches Serum und/oder menschliches Plasma gewonnen wird, wobei in dem Verfahren Albumin und IgG voneinander getrennt werden, wobei das Verfahren die Schritte umfasst:
a) wahlweises Anpassen des pH-Wertes der Proteinlösung an einen vorgegebenen pH-Wert;
b) wahlweises Anpassen der Ionenstärke oder der Leitfähigkeit der Proteinlösung an eine vorgegebene Ionenstärke oder an eine vorgegebene Leitfähigkeit;
c) Anwenden der Proteinlösung auf eine Adsorptionssäule, die ein Adsorbens umfasst, wobei das Adsorbens ein Teilchen mit mindestens einem nicht porösen Kern hoher Dichte umfasst, der von einem porösen Material umgeben ist, und wobei das Adsorbens eine Teilchendichte von mindestens 1,5 g/ml und einen mittleren Durchmesser des Teilchenvolumens von höchstens 150 µm umfasst;
d) Waschen von einem oder mehreren der Proteine, die durch das Adsorbens isoliert werden sollen, ohne dass das eine oder die mehreren der Proteine spezifisch an das Adsorbens gebunden worden sind, um eine nicht gebundene Materialfraktion zu erhalten;
e) Unterwerfen des Adsorbens einem Elutionspuffer, um mindestens eines der Proteine, das spezifisch an das Adsorbens gebunden ist, zu eluieren;
wobei entweder:
Albumin und IgG aus dem Adsorbens durch eine stufenweise Elution erhalten werden; oder Albumin als nicht gebundenes Material aus dem Adsorbens erhalten wird und anschließend IgG aus dem Adsorbens durch eine stufenweise Elution erhalten wird.

A process for the large-scale isolation of proteins from a protein solution wherein the protein solution is obtained from human blood, such as human serum and/or human plasma, in which process albumin and IgG are separated from one another, said process comprising the steps of:
a) optionally adjusting the pH of the protein solution to a preset pH;
b) optionally adjusting the ionic strength or conductivity of the protein solution to a preset ionic strength or a preset conductivity;
c) applying said protein solution to an adsorption column comprising an adsorbent, said adsorbent comprises a particle with at least one high density nonporous core, surrounded by a porous material, the adsorbent comprises a particle density of at least 1.5 g/ml and a mean volume particle diameter of at most 150 µm;
d) washing one or more of the proteins to be isolated through the adsorbent, without the one or more proteins having been specifically bound to the adsorbent, to obtain a non-bound material fraction;
e) subjecting the adsorbent to an elution buffer to elute at least one of the proteins specifically bound to the adsorbent;
wherein either:
albumin and IgG are obtained from the adsorbent by stepwise elution; or
albumin is obtained as non-bound material from the adsorbent and subsequently IgG is obtained from the adsorbent by stepwise elution.

Procédé pour l'isolation à grande échelle de protéines à partir d'une solution de protéine dans lequel la solution de protéine est obtenue à partir du sang humain, tel que le sérum humain et/ou le plasma humain, au cours duquel l'albumine et l'IgG sont séparés l'un de l'autre, ledit procédé se composant des étapes de:
a) ajustage optionnel du pH de la solution de protéine à un pH présélectionné;
b) ajustage optionnel de la force ionique ou de la conductivité de la solution de protéine à une force ionique présélectionnée ou une conductivité présélectionnée;
c) application de ladite solution de protéine sur une colonne d'adsorption comprenant un adsorbant, ledit adsorbant comprenant une particule avec au moins un noyau non poreux à densité élevée, entouré par un matériau poreux, l'adsorbant comprenant une densité de particule d'au moins 1,5 g/ml et un diamètre de particule volumique moyen d'au plus 150 µm;
d) lavage d'une ou plusieurs protéines devant être isolées à travers l'adsorbant, sans que les protéines uniques ou multiples aient été spécifiquement liées à l'adsorbant, pour obtenir une fraction de matériau non lié;
e) soumission de l'adsorbant à un tampon d'élution pour éluer au moins une des protéines spécifiquement liée à l'adsorbant;
dans lequel:
l'albumine et l'IgG sont obtenus à partir de l'adsorbant par élution progressive; ou
l'albumine est obtenue comme un matériau non lié à partir de l'adsorbant et ensuite l'IgG est obtenue à partir de l'adsorbant par élution par progressive
